  "title": "Banana Bread Overnight Oats",
  "subtitle": "Mostly waiting, mostly worth it.",
  "excerpt": "Banana Bread Overnight Oats. A home-cook's recipe from Rebecca's collection, kept in the family rotation.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook. Bread recipes draw on the long tradition of home baking, Elizabeth David's English Bread and Yeast Cookery is one of the canonical references in English.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Banana Bread Overnight Oats. A British home-cook's dish, the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bread is mostly waiting. Mix, prove, shape, prove again, bake hot with steam.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
