      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mash the banana in the bottom of a bowl or jar that can be sealed. Combine all other ingredients and stir well to combine.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Refrigerate overnight or at least about 4 hours. Serve hot or cold.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Garnish with some sliced banana or more nuts if desired.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Notes",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sweeten these banana bread overnight oats to your liking. The banana already adds a decent amount of sweet. I go back and forth on the maple--sometimes I just add a drizzle in the morning when serving.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "I find that overnight oats with bananas are best if eaten within 3 days. If you want to make these for the week, add the mashed banana in just before serving for any servings that won't be eaten until day 4 or 5.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "You can easily make these banana overnight oats vegan by using dairy free milk. For gluten free, make sure the oats are certified gluten free.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Warm them up in the morning for a hot breakfast",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Check yeast in warm water with a pinch of sugar. It should froth in five minutes. Prove in a warm spot (airing cupboard or oven with the light on).",
              "cause": "Yeast was stale, or the dough was too cold.",
              "symptom": "Bread is dense and didn't rise"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Preheat to 220°C with a tray on the bottom. Throw a cup of water into the tray when the loaf goes in, steam gives crust.",
              "cause": "Oven not hot enough, or no steam.",
              "symptom": "Crust is pale and soft"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Give it longer, until the dough doesn't spring back when poked. Shape gently so the bubbles survive.",
              "cause": "Underproved, or the dough was knocked back too hard.",
              "symptom": "Open crumb wasn't open"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Bake on a heavier tray on the middle shelf. Lining with baking paper helps.",
              "cause": "Tray was too thin, or rack too low.",
              "symptom": "Bottom burnt before top browned"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Seeded crust: brush the top with water and roll in mixed seeds before the final prove.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Wholemeal: replace 100 g of the flour with wholemeal for a denser, nuttier loaf.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sits well in the fridge overnight; see the method for the chilling step. Designed as a make-ahead: assemble the night before, eat in the morning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
